## M19(2/6): raw `%x` access outside an unsafe context is rejected.
##
## Per GPT-5.5 entry 35 (M19 design): raw access is the
## archetypal unsafe operation. Without an enclosing `unsafe`
## block OR an `unsafe` fn declaration, the operation is sema-
## rejected with a tailored diagnostic pointing the user at
## both fixes.

sub main()
  x = 7
  r = %x           # error: raw access outside unsafe context
